commit.message:
Fix the display table for Lao braille yaml tests

The yaml tests for Lao braille use a plain
table (latinLetterDef6Dots.uti) in the display table. This is very
fishy and naturally fails in louis-rs.

So I converted the yaml test to use a "normal" display table using
only display opcodes.

commit.message:
Fix ) sign in grade 1 table

This started failing after an update to the UEB table.

This change also fixes a back-translation issue.
Mark a test that started failing after rebase
Fix back-translation of capital letters

Run tests in both directions

Back-translation failures are marked with `{xfail: {backward:
conflict}}' (in case of failures that are due to conflicts and can not
be resolved) or `{xfail: {backward: true}}` in case of resolvable
back-translation issues.

Signed-off-by: Attila Hammer <hammera@pickup.hu>
